# Circuit Design System — Mandatory Rules

Before writing any UI code, you MUST look up the latest tokens and components from the installed Circuit DS package. Never rely on memorized or hardcoded lists — the package evolves.

**CRITICAL: Never import PrimeVue components directly when a Circuit DS custom component exists that wraps or replaces it.** Circuit DS has two types of components:
1. **Custom components** — Circuit-built wrappers with enhanced behavior. Import from `@jumpcloud/circuit/components`.
2. **Primitives (PT-styled)** — PrimeVue components styled by Circuit's passthrough theme. Only use these directly from `primevue/*` when NO Circuit custom wrapper exists.

## 1. Typography — Use Circuit Tokens Only

Never use raw Tailwind text sizes (`text-base`, `text-2xl`), arbitrary values (`text-[14px]`), custom `leading-*`, or inline `font-size` styles.

**How to find available typography tokens:**
- Read the Tailwind preset: `node_modules/@jumpcloud/circuit/dist/tailwind/index.cjs` — look for `fontSize` keys.
- Search for `text-body-` and `text-heading-` patterns in Circuit's dist to discover all current type scale tokens.
- Check existing Circuit component source files in `node_modules/@jumpcloud/circuit/dist/components/` for real usage examples.

```html
<!-- ❌ WRONG -->
<h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold leading-8">Title</h1>

<!-- ✅ CORRECT — use a Circuit heading token -->
<h1 class="text-heading-2">Title</h1>
<p class="text-body-md">Body</p>
```

## 2. Colors — Use Circuit Tokens Only, No Exceptions

Never use hardcoded hex (`text-[#0f202f]`), rgba (`text-[rgba(...)]`), raw Tailwind palette colors (`text-gray-500`, `bg-white`), or inline `color`/`background-color` styles.

**How to find available color tokens:**
- Read the Tailwind preset: `node_modules/@jumpcloud/circuit/dist/tailwind/index.cjs` — look for `colors`, `backgroundColor`, `textColor`, `borderColor` keys to discover all semantic token names.
- Search for `--jc-color-` CSS custom properties in Circuit's dist files to find the full semantic color system.
- Token naming follows the pattern: `{utility}-{component}-{variant}` (e.g. `bg-neutral-surface`, `text-button-primary-base`, `border-field-default`).

```html
<!-- ❌ WRONG -->
<div class="bg-white text-[#0f202f] border-[#e7e9ea]">
<span class="text-gray-500">Subtle</span>

<!-- ✅ CORRECT — use Circuit semantic tokens -->
<div class="bg-neutral-surface text-neutral-base border-neutral-default_solid">
<span class="text-neutral-subtle">Subtle</span>
```

## 3. Components — Always Use Circuit DS Components, NEVER Raw PrimeVue

**NEVER import a PrimeVue component directly if Circuit DS provides a custom wrapper for it.** Always prefer the Circuit custom component.

### 3a. Circuit Custom Components (import from `@jumpcloud/circuit/components`)

These wrap or replace PrimeVue primitives with Circuit-specific behavior, styling, and API. **Always use these instead of their PrimeVue equivalents.**

| Circuit Custom Component | Replaces PrimeVue | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `CollapsiblePanel` | `Panel` | Use for all card/panel sections. Supports `toggleable` prop for collapsible behavior. |
| `MessageNotification` | `Message` | Use `title` and `detail` props instead of default slot. |
| `CheckboxWithLabel` | `Checkbox` | Use when checkbox needs a label (most cases). Has `#label` and `#description` slots. |
| `DataTable` | `DataTable` + `Column` | Takes a `columns` prop array instead of `<Column>` children. |
| `DataTableToolbar` | — | Toolbar for DataTable with search, filters, slots. |
| `DataTableCellText` | — | Cell renderer for text columns. |
| `DataTableCellLink` | — | Cell renderer for link columns. |
| `DataTableCellToken` | — | Cell renderer for status token columns. |
| `DataTableCellButton` | — | Cell renderer for button columns. |
| `ToggleSwitch` | `ToggleSwitch` | Circuit-styled toggle. |
| `Paginator` | `Paginator` | Circuit-styled paginator. |
| `Chip` | `Chip` | Circuit-styled chip. |
| `Password` | `Password` | Circuit-styled password input. |
| `ProgressSpinner` | `ProgressSpinner` | Circuit-styled spinner. |
| `ToastNotification` | `Toast` | Circuit-styled toast messages. |
| `RadioButtonWithLabel` | `RadioButton` | Use when radio button needs a label. |
| `InputOtp` | `InputOtp` | Circuit-styled OTP input. |
| `SelectWithSlots` | `Select` | Use when select needs custom slot content. |
| `Dropdown` | — | Circuit dropdown component. |
| `ExportDropdown` | — | Export functionality dropdown. |
| `SavedViewsDropdown` | — | Saved views management. |
| `ColumnConfigDropdown` | — | Column configuration. |
| `FormField` | — | Form field wrapper with label, validation, description. |
| `FilterModal` | — | Filter modal dialog. |
| `FilterField` | — | Individual filter field. |
| `FilterButton` | — | Button to open filters. |
| `FilterChip` | — | Active filter chip. |
| `LinkText` | — | Styled link text. |
| `CardButton` | — | Card-style button. |
| `AppNavigation` | — | App-level left navigation. |
| `PageHeader` | — | Page header with tabs, actions, breadcrumbs. |
| `SaveViewPanel` | — | Panel for saving views. |

```ts
// ✅ CORRECT — import from Circuit
import { CollapsiblePanel, MessageNotification, CheckboxWithLabel, DataTable } from '@jumpcloud/circuit/components';

// ❌ WRONG — never use these directly when Circuit wraps them
import Panel from 'primevue/panel';
import Message from 'primevue/message';
import Checkbox from 'primevue/checkbox';
import DataTable from 'primevue/datatable';
```

### 3b. Circuit DS Primitive Components (import from `primevue/*`)

These ARE Circuit DS components. Circuit owns and styles them via passthrough (PT) configs at `@jumpcloud/circuit/src/primevue-primitives/`. They are imported from `primevue/*` but they are part of Circuit DS. Use these when no Circuit custom wrapper exists:

`Avatar`, `Badge`, `Button`, `Dialog`, `Divider`, `Drawer`, `IconField`, `InputGroup`, `InputText`, `Menu`, `MultiSelect`, `Popover`, `RadioButton` (without label), `RadioButtonGroup`, `Select` (without slots), `SelectButton`, `Skeleton`, `Tabs`/`TabList`/`Tab`/`TabPanels`/`TabPanel`, `Tag`, `Textarea`, `TieredMenu`, `Tooltip`

```ts
// ✅ CORRECT — Circuit DS primitives, imported from primevue but styled by Circuit
import Button from 'primevue/button';
import Tag from 'primevue/tag';
import SelectButton from 'primevue/selectbutton';
import Dialog from 'primevue/dialog';
```

**How to verify:** Check `node_modules/@jumpcloud/circuit/dist/src/primevue-primitives/` for the full list of Circuit DS primitive components. If a `.js` file exists there, the component is part of Circuit DS.

### 3c. Icons

```ts
import { IconName } from '@jumpcloud/icons';
import { IconName } from '@heroicons/vue/24/outline';
```

### 3d. Component Not Found?

**If a needed component does not exist in Circuit DS (neither custom nor PT-styled), ASK the user** whether to create a new reusable component or use a one-off solution. Never silently build a duplicate.

## 4. Figma Code Connect — Finding the Right Component

When implementing from a Figma design, use the Figma MCP server's Code Connect features before writing any code:

1. **`get_code_connect_map`** — Pass the Figma node ID to get mapped component source paths and names.
2. **`get_code_connect_suggestions`** — Get suggestions for linking a Figma node to code components.
3. **`get_design_context`** — Get full design context including component structure and styling.

Always check Code Connect first to find the correct Circuit component and its import path. Use the mapped component exactly as specified.

## 5. Spacing & Border Radius

Never use arbitrary spacing (`p-[12px]`) or radius (`rounded-[8px]`) values.

**How to find available tokens:**
- Read the Tailwind preset for `spacing` and `borderRadius` keys to discover all Circuit aliases (e.g. `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`).

## 6. Pre-Implementation Checklist

Before writing any UI code, always:
1. Look up current Circuit typography tokens from the Tailwind preset.
2. Look up current Circuit color tokens from the Tailwind preset.
3. Check `@jumpcloud/circuit/components` exports FIRST for a custom component match.
4. If no custom component exists, check `primevue-primitives/` for a PT-styled primitive.
5. If implementing from Figma, check Code Connect first via the MCP server.
6. If no matching component exists in Circuit DS at all, ask the user before creating a new one.
